	<p>Welcome to ColorLab.  To acheive exactly the color you want, you need to know where you are starting (current level) and where you want to be (desired level).  We often see ourselves diffently than what the color manufacturer considers "dark brown" or "light blonde" for example; so use the swatches below to find the closest match</p>
	<p>Covering grey is a rather exacting science.  Use the swatches below to find your percentage of grey. The app will advise amounts of neutral color to use for your color.  This means that if you want to be "Dark Golden Blonde" and you are using 2 oz of color, a certain percentage of the mix has to be neutral.  An example formula for "Dark Golden Blonde" when you are 50% grey is 1 oz of 6N and 1 oz of 6G for the best coverage and tonality.</p>
